{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"60569487-13ce-4757-9fc5-59f6f08edc58","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload)\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — run only tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"DisplayName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c3430b79-6081-48d3-83d6-a6fee69283b3","outputTokens":166,"requestId":"1BF3:23CF76:24C87F7:28A7F95:6A03DDBA"},"id":"c3667a07-a570-4fc7-b2c7-1e67536f3115","timestamp":"2026-05-13T02:11:13.074Z","parentId":"9238c288-8e56-4bbc-8df1-d97abc7f8d64"}
